21 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
22 SECTION 1. AMENDATORY 50 O.S. 2021, Section 2, is
23 amended to read as follows:
24
ENGR. S. A. TO ENGR. H. B. NO. 2622 Page 1
1 Section 2. A public nuisance is one which affects at the same
2 time an entire community or neighborhood, or any considerable number
3 of persons, although the extent of the annoyance or damage inflicted
4 upon the individuals may be unequal. The manufacturing, marketing,
5 and selling of lawful products shall not be deemed a public
6 nuisance.
7 SECTION 2. AMENDATORY 50 O.S. 2021, Section 8, is
8 amended to read as follows:
9 Section 8. A. The remedies against a public nuisance are:
10 1. Indictment or information, or;
11 2. A civil action, or seeking injunctive or other equitable
12 relief; or
13 3. Abatement;.
14 B. To be found liable in an action for public nuisance, the
15 defendant in such an action must be determined by the court to have
16 been in control of the conditions giving rise to the nuisance at the
17 time of injury.
18 SECTION 3. AMENDATORY 50 O.S. 2021, Section 10, is
19 amended to read as follows:
20 Section 10. A private person may maintain an action for a
21 public nuisance if it the court determines by clear and convincing
22 evidence that the nuisance is specially injurious the proximate
23 cause of special injury to himself the private person, but not
24 otherwise.
ENGR. S. A. TO ENGR. H. B. NO. 2622 Page 2
1 SECTION 4. AMENDATORY 50 O.S. 2021, Section 21, is
2 amended to read as follows:
3 Section 21. The repeated use of any real property or structure
4 thereon to commit unlawful drug distribution, prostitution, human
5 trafficking, or sex trafficking acts which result in a felony
6 conviction under the Oklahoma Uniform Controlled Dangerous
7 Substances Act may shall constitute a public nuisance.
8 SECTION 5. This act shall become effective November 1, 2025.”
9 Passed the Senate the 8th day of May, 2025.
